# Traffic Light Controller

## Objective
To simulate an intelligent traffic signal system using Arduino.

## Components Required

- Arduino UNO
- 3 LEDs (Red, Yellow, Green)
- 3 × 220Ω Resistors
- Push Button
- Breadboard
- Jumper Wires

## Connections

| Component | Pin |
|-----------|-----|
| Red LED | D8 |
| Yellow LED | D9 |
| Green LED | D10 |
| Button | D7 |

## Working Principle

The traffic signal follows the sequence:

RED → YELLOW → GREEN

A pedestrian button connected to pin D7 allows pedestrians to request crossing. When pressed, the system immediately switches to RED and holds it for 8 seconds.

## Serial Output Example

```text
[0 ms] RED
[5000 ms] YELLOW
[7000 ms] GREEN
[11000 ms] Pedestrian Crossing - RED
